##Hubei's vegetables, no place to put

Micro-signal. Meirirenwu

Functional Introduction, light business, understand life.

Recently, Hubei Vegetable farmers to Pin Hong often insomnia, 4:00 am to get up to hold a flashlight to turn around the vegetable plot. He knew that the 1,000 acres of vegetables were hopeless.

In Hubei, a large vegetable province, there are countless vegetable farmers in the same situation as Xiang Pinhong. On the night of March 2, vegetable farmer Li Daocui's son asked for help at a local forum. "A few thousand catties of garlic shoots are sleeping on the ground. It's Ok to give them away. ".

Outside the village gates, where the outbreak has sealed off one by one, demand for vegetables is rising and people want to buy fresh, cheap vegetables. On the afternoon of March 3, residents of Zhongxiang, where Li's family lives, put out a call on the forum: "I hope the vegetables of the farmer's uncle will come to town as soon as possible to meet the needs of the residents. "

We interviewed three Hubei Vegetable farmers. Their city, in Jianghan Plain, is known as "The valley. " . Locally grown vegetables are sold to Beijing, Guangdong, Chongqing and Shaanxi before being served on the dinner table. They love rotten vegetables in the field, the biggest wish is that the day of unsealing, if sell the best vegetables, how low the price is OK.

Here are three vegetable farmers'statements.

By Dan Cheng

Editor | Cho Ming
Run | Yifan

"It's none of our business how much the food has gone up. "

Li Shichun, a Jingshan County vegetable farmer, 53

I am a 53-year-old vegetable farmer in Jingshan, Hubei Province. I am also the director and secretary of the village committee of Xinhekou village. 500 Mu of land, used to grow vegetables and medicinal materials, of which 20 mu of Chinese cabbage, 180 Mu of snow potherb mustard, 300 mu of Pinellia, originally thought this year will be a bumper harvest, but did not think of the epidemic came.

On December twenty-eight, the town suddenly held a meeting to inform the epidemic prevention and control of matters needing attention. At that time there were 360 people from our village back from Wuhan, I was very scared, did not think about the food in my mind, quickly tied a rope to the speaker in the roof of the car, back to the village door to door shouting. New Year, everyone came back, when the villagers did not wear masks, exploded, said it might not be so serious. I said to you: "The coronavirus is very serious, is not kidding, only lives once. "

At first they didn't think it was such a big deal, but after watching a lot of TV, they went along with it.

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, at my suggestion, our village was the first to implement road closure.

Besides me, there were twenty vegetable farmers in the village, a few tens of Mu less, a few hundred mu more. After I closed the village, someone asked me what to do about the food? I am also puzzled, no way, to say loss, the village I lost the most, 20 mu of Chinese cabbage and 180 Mu of potherb mustard are planted in the field, and catch up with the drought last year, the cost of growing vegetables has doubled.

For example, an Acre of land in fertilizer, pumping, buying pipes, manual care costs 1,000 yuan, when the drought will be 2,000 yuan, add up to a loss of two hundred and seventy thousand. But I can not say this, I have to say: "is the food important or life important? Can only say that when the unsealed, we find a way to get everyone's dishes out again. "

This isn't the first time I've lost money. In 2014, I started planting roses, planted 100 Mu at a stretch, the first year of planting, the second year of long branches, to the third year in May finally emerged red buds. At that time had signed a contract with the outside boss, 4 yuan more money a catty, the expected investment of 3 million yuan capital can certainly earn back, in a particularly good mood.

As a result, it began to rain in May. It rained for a whole month. The roses could not see so much water. By the next month, it began to rain heavily. Within five days, our village was flooded, and the pigsty on one of the village's pig farms was blown down by the water, hundreds of pigs were washed away, floating in the water.

Our place is a plain at five meters above sea level, next to the river. It is easy to be flooded. I went to see my rose bed, which was already under water, and the Red Buds and the green leaves and the garbage of the village were floating on the dirty water. It was an ocean.

I don't even remember what it was like. I was a big man and I cried. There's no use crying. This is the worst loss of my life. My wife was upset with me, and she was depressed.

Mature vegetables can not be shipped out, is not rotten in the field or after the harvest Tuen together. Image / Oriental

In 2016, I scraped together 400,000 yuan from relatives and friends, plus another 1.68 million yuan from my own savings, and started to learn to grow vegetables from Zhong Xiang next door. Chinese cabbage and potherb mustard are high-profit vegetables, planted in October, during the Chinese New Year can be sold at a good price, Chinese cabbage usually 1 yuan 1 kg, before and after the Spring Festival can be sold for 1.5 yuan, potherb mustard is generally 3 to 5 cents a catty, but it has a short cycle and can be planted twice a year.

We have regular partners who drive long-distance trucks from the north to the villages and can empty them all at once. These vegetables are sold to the north, including Beijing, Shandong, Heilongjiang and other places. With my help, thirty families in the village started growing vegetables on a large scale, which has been profitable for several years. Before the Chinese New Year everyone is busy. In December or so, when the big cars drive in, the land is filled with people, picking, harvesting and packing.

After the sale of the vegetables, we farmers often go out to dinner and drink to celebrate, who sell well who treat. All 502 families in the village hung two big Red Lanterns and played cards with relatives all night long. The roads are full of people, the traffic is bad, it's very busy.

But now the village is deserted, the roads are empty, and police cars patrol the streets, urging people to stay at home. I've lived in the village half my life, and I've never seen anything like it, and suddenly the world feels quiet.

I have to drive to the village every day to patrol, the fields are not a lot of people, sometimes pass my field to see, a large green Wang Wang, cabbage wrapped tightly, the middle has been in Bloom Long White Moss. Once the CABBAGE MOSS will be lower price, can not save. This year Zhongxiang area vegetables also lost a lot, a friend's cooperative, 700 mu vegetables trapped in the village transport can not go out, all rotten in the field, can only at home sigh, no way.

The fifth day of the first month, the above notice if the villagers have any demand, let the village director on the street on behalf of the purchase. So we started to build wechat group that day, the village of 5 groups to form 5 wechat group, we need to list the materials, I count good in the street supermarket to buy. There aren't enough people in the supermarket. It's all hands on deck. I had to pick it out myself. It's funny, at first it was rice, grain and oil, and then the women in the village told me to buy Sanitary Napkins. I did not buy half of life, what do not know, at first or let the supermarket people to help me choose, and then bought more, Sanitary Napkins these brands, day and night use, how much are ripe.

Every day to buy a bill, small bills have more than two feet long, densely is word, go back to the car co-pilot, back seat, the trunk are also stuffed full, back to the village each take goods.

I often eat instant noodles in the village when I'm busy, and they give me canker sores. I don't know how much the price of food has gone up outside, but it's none of our business. We can't get our food out anyway.

If there is demand in the village, go to the vegetable farmer's field to pick, anyway put there is also bad. Even so, not many people picked them.

The time for spring plowing is coming. We must make room for corn and soybeans. One year's harvest has been ruined, and the next one can not be delayed.

The crops still in the field need to be disposed of in order not to affect the spring ploughing. Image / video capture

"wholesalers in the provinces say Hubei food is not allowed. "

Samara farmer Xiang Pinhong, 50

Four million dollars. I've been growing vegetables for seven years, and I've never lost this much. Cabbage 340 mu, cabbage 150 mu, radish 80 mu, lettuce 150 mu, Artemisia 90 mu, all rotten in the field.

Our village has access to trucks, and the main problem is that we can't find staff to help. On the first day of the New Year, the village told everyone to stay at home. On February 20, I made a list. Two big lorries came from Jingmen to load lettuce. I called the farmers and told them to load the lettuce. I went back to the village clerk to help coordinate, and only 15 people showed up.

But these people will not pack, mainly responsible for the shed of lettuce to the car, each person also maintain a distance of 4 meters, much less efficient. The lettuces were in flower, so we had to pick out 40 acres that weren't in flower. It's more than a buck a kilo as usual. I'll sell it for 60 cents this time. When they pull it out, the price is different. It's supposed to be $1.70 a kilo.

Chinese cabbage used to be must be packed, tied with a rope, selling vegetables must be packaged a little beautiful to sell. This time there's no hands, just take it to the van and get rid of it for a few cents a kilo.

At this time of year, we're completely empty, and it's not enough. I need to borrow a few thousand acres from another co-op to satisfy my customers. Every day there are several large trucks in and out pull vegetables, every day at least 70 tons of processing, sold to Beijing, Guangzhou, Chongqing, Shaanxi, Shanxi, Shandong and other places.

Now there are only three customers, mostly local wholesalers in Jingmen. Many places can not get out, said a car stuck in the mouth of the village, or in the road block up more than one meter high Earth Dam do not let go.

Ten days ago, a wholesaler in Wuhan asked me for a batch of Chinese cabbage. He got a big truck from another place to pull 18 tons of Chinese cabbage. He refused to let me pass on the way back. Finally, he had no way to make a detour and ran an extra eighty kilometers.

Cars from other provinces couldn't get in. I called the wholesalers that Guangzhou and Chongqing often work with. They said Hubei was a disaster area, so they couldn't get food from Hubei, and they couldn't.

Watching the food go bad day by day makes me sad. More than 100 Mu of Artemisia Sphaerocephala are now Rotary Tiller spin off. The last time I turned the lettuce in the shed, my wife was standing there crying and not saying anything. The vegetables, which were planted last August, employ thirty workers a day and cost more than 2,000 yuan per mu of land.

Hubei is a big vegetable province, too many people grow vegetables, the price of vegetables also can not go up, I have lost for 3 years in a row.

These two days, we are going to use the land we used to grow Artemisia to grow Chili peppers, so we moved to live near the vegetable fields. Worry Ah, a day 3 packs of cigarettes can not stop, night smoking more, can not sleep has been watching TV, open TV are talking about the epidemic. I woke up at 4:00 in the morning, got up, held a flashlight and went to the vegetable plot to see how bad the food was. It was dark outside, and there were only a few birdcalls now and then, and I was walking alone in the vegetable patch.

Spring ploughing is coming. There is not much money to be put into it now. When the time comes, we will borrow some more from our relatives and friends. We have lent some money in the past. We are all too embarrassed to ask. Let us consider these matters after a period of time. For the time being, we will free up more than 1,000 mu of land.

After the outbreak was closed to management, village committees or communities in a position to do so helped farmers find ways to sell their vegetables. Screenshot of the cover news video

"150 catties of Seaweed Moss donated to the city. "

Chung cheung-choi, Lee do-chui, 48

On the morning of the first day of the New Year, more than 10:00 am, the village suddenly stopped a silver-gray car, the loudspeaker announced that the village closed, I just know the city that pneumonia serious.

At lunch time, his wife sighed and said, "If we keep closing the village, how can we get our food out? " At that time, there were nearly 3 mu of garlic plants in our field that had not yet grown up and were not even tied up to 1 kg. Our family a total of 6 mu 8 field, other cabbage, radish scattered scattered planted a mu or two mu, usually after the sale of vegetables. I think the food is almost done, and the village is unsealed.

Turns out, I didn't think it would be this bad.

The garlic in the field adds up to nearly 6000 Jin, began to grow moss slowly, my wife and I are anxious, every day to remove grass, pull moss. Garlic is very tired, from the beginning of the lunar calendar in July sowing, after several times weeding, to now pull moss, we have to bend one by one, one day down backache, small business, reluctant to find workers help, when the time is not easy to calculate.

Our entire village of Liangqiao village 12 groups of more than 60 households, young people have gone outside, the remaining old people mainly to plant garlic seedlings, together there are nearly 100 mu garlic seedlings, this loss is very big.

As usual, after Chinese New Year, the two of US tied up all the garlic seedlings in the field. My wife would drive a tricycle to pull 200-300 Jin, walk more than 20 minutes to the city and set up a stall. During Chinese New Year, the price in the city could rise to 1 yuan per Jin, almost every day can be sold out, months to time all the garlic can be emptied.

We have no channel to sell vegetables, I heard that these days outside of the food sold very expensive. We don't know the greengrocers, we know the big platforms, but they don't know us. Usually pull themselves to the city to sell scattered, sometimes met the boss, as long as take more, lower prices, we also sell, can not let the vegetables bad in the field. In this way, the garlic shoots can be sold for more than 10,000 yuan a year. Years ago also think, this year to sell the garlic seedlings, to buy some goods, usually want to eat expensive things, only in the new year to buy.

My wife and I grow vegetables for a year's income. My son runs a small restaurant in the city that specializes in crispy-skin chicken and roast rice. He takes take-out food. He sleeps at 3 a.m. and gets up at 8 a.m. or 9 a.m. every day. His daughter-in-law works all night as a waitress at a KTV, they earn enough to feed themselves, and they work hard. Black eye is very heavy, but also to pay the mortgage, usually no time to come back, sometimes we will carry vegetables to the city to see them, also do not dare to disturb.

This year they came back to the original plan to leave the third day, but closed the village did not go. Actually, I'm very happy, as a family. I told my son how much I cherish these days.

A few days ago, the son posted a post on the Internet, the photo of our garlic plant uploaded, the next day there are many people to call us, said to want garlic plant. I am very glad, take advantage of the garlic sprout does not have full length moss, still can handle out. But then I couldn't even negotiate the price, so I couldn't. The main thing is, they can't get their cars in, we can't get them out, and we still haven't sold them for a dime.

For us, such retail investors, there is not too much impact, but the next year the quality of life is a little worse than we lost many people.

On the 15th day of the first lunar month, the village committee launched a donation meeting. We donated 100 yuan by mobile phone, and then pulled 150 catties of Seaweed Moss to the brigade. They then pulled out to donate to the community in the city.

If the vegetable really sell out, we also accept, the son often said, as long as we are saved, the vegetable does not sell out does not matter.

I think so, but still want to unseal, this garlic can sell the best, how low price is OK.

At that time there were 360 people from our village back from Wuhan, I was very scared, did not think about the food in my mind, quickly tied a rope to the speaker in the roof of the car, back to the village door to door shouting. New Year, everyone came back, when the villagers did not wear masks, exploded, said it might not be so serious. I said to you: "The coronavirus is very serious, is not kidding, only lives once. "

At first they didn't think it was such a big deal, but after watching a lot of TV, they went along with it.

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, at my suggestion, our village was the first to implement road closure.

Besides me, there were twenty vegetable farmers in the village, a few tens of Mu less, a few hundred mu more. After I closed the village, someone asked me what to do about the food? I am also puzzled, no way, to say loss, the village I lost the most, 20 mu of Chinese cabbage and 180 Mu of potherb mustard are planted in the field, and catch up with the drought last year, the cost of growing vegetables has doubled.

For example, an Acre of land in fertilizer, pumping, buying pipes, manual care costs 1,000 yuan, when the drought will be 2,000 yuan, add up to a loss of two hundred and seventy thousand. But I can not say this, I have to say: "is the food important or life important? Can only say that when the unsealed, we find a way to get everyone's dishes out again. "

This isn't the first time I've lost money. In 2014, I started planting roses, planted 100 Mu at a stretch, the first year of planting, the second year of long branches, to the third year in May finally emerged red buds. At that time had signed a contract with the outside boss, 4 yuan more money a catty, the expected investment of 3 million yuan capital can certainly earn back, in a particularly good mood.

As a result, it began to rain in May. It rained for a whole month. The roses could not see so much water. By the next month, it began to rain heavily. Within five days, our village was flooded, and the pigsty on one of the village's pig farms was blown down by the water, hundreds of pigs were washed away, floating in the water.

Our place is a plain at five meters above sea level, next to the river. It is easy to be flooded. I went to see my rose bed, which was already under water, and the Red Buds and the green leaves and the garbage of the village were floating on the dirty water. It was an ocean.

I don't even remember what it was like. I was a big man and I cried. There's no use crying. This is the worst loss of my life. My wife was upset with me, and she was depressed.

Mature vegetables can not be shipped out, is not rotten in the field or after the harvest Tuen together. Image / Oriental

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In 2016, I scraped together 400,000 yuan from relatives and friends, plus another 1.68 million yuan from my own savings, and started to learn to grow vegetables from Zhong Xiang next door. Chinese cabbage and potherb mustard are high-profit vegetables, planted in October, during the Chinese New Year can be sold at a good price, Chinese cabbage usually 1 yuan 1 kg, before and after the Spring Festival can be sold for 1.5 yuan, potherb mustard is generally 3 to 5 cents a catty, but it has a short cycle and can be planted twice a year.

We have regular partners who drive long-distance trucks from the north to the villages and can empty them all at once. These vegetables are sold to the north, including Beijing, Shandong, Heilongjiang and other places. With my help, thirty families in the village started growing vegetables on a large scale, which has been profitable for several years. Before the Chinese New Year everyone is busy. In December or so, when the big cars drive in, the land is filled with people, picking, harvesting and packing.

After the sale of the vegetables, we farmers often go out to dinner and drink to celebrate, who sell well who treat. All 502 families in the village hung two big Red Lanterns and played cards with relatives all night long. The roads are full of people, the traffic is bad, it's very busy.

But now the village is deserted, the roads are empty, and police cars patrol the streets, urging people to stay at home. I've lived in the village half my life, and I've never seen anything like it, and suddenly the world feels quiet.

I have to drive to the village every day to patrol, the fields are not a lot of people, sometimes pass my field to see, a large green Wang Wang, cabbage wrapped tightly, the middle has been in Bloom Long White Moss. Once the CABBAGE MOSS will be lower price, can not save. This year Zhongxiang area vegetables also lost a lot, a friend's cooperative, 700 mu vegetables trapped in the village transport can not go out, all rotten in the field, can only at home sigh, no way.

The fifth day of the first month, the above notice if the villagers have any demand, let the village director on the street on behalf of the purchase. So we started to build wechat group that day, the village of 5 groups to form 5 wechat group, we need to list the materials, I count good in the street supermarket to buy. There aren't enough people in the supermarket. It's all hands on deck. I had to pick it out myself. It's funny, at first it was rice, grain and oil, and then the women in the village told me to buy Sanitary Napkins. I did not buy half of life, what do not know, at first or let the supermarket people to help me choose, and then bought more, Sanitary Napkins these brands, day and night use, how much are ripe.

Every day to buy a bill, small bills have more than two feet long, densely is word, go back to the car co-pilot, back seat, the trunk are also stuffed full, back to the village each take goods.

I often eat instant noodles in the village when I'm busy, and they give me canker sores. I don't know how much the price of food has gone up outside, but it's none of our business. We can't get our food out anyway.

If there is demand in the village, go to the vegetable farmer's field to pick, anyway put there is also bad. Even so, not many people picked them.

The time for spring plowing is coming. We must make room for corn and soybeans. One year's harvest has been ruined, and the next one can not be delayed.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The crops still in the field need to be disposed of in order not to affect the spring ploughing. Image / video capture

"wholesalers in the provinces say Hubei food is not allowed. "

Samara farmer Xiang Pinhong, 50

Four million dollars. I've been growing vegetables for seven years, and I've never lost this much. Cabbage 340 mu, cabbage 150 mu, radish 80 mu, lettuce 150 mu, Artemisia 90 mu, all rotten in the field.

Our village has access to trucks, and the main problem is that we can't find staff to help. On the first day of the New Year, the village told everyone to stay at home. On February 20, I made a list. Two big lorries came from Jingmen to load lettuce. I called the farmers and told them to load the lettuce. I went back to the village clerk to help coordinate, and only 15 people showed up.

But these people will not pack, mainly responsible for the shed of lettuce to the car, each person also maintain a distance of 4 meters, much less efficient. The lettuces were in flower, so we had to pick out 40 acres that weren't in flower. It's more than a buck a kilo as usual. I'll sell it for 60 cents this time. When they pull it out, the price is different. It's supposed to be $1.70 a kilo.

Chinese cabbage used to be must be packed, tied with a rope, selling vegetables must be packaged a little beautiful to sell. This time there's no hands, just take it to the van and get rid of it for a few cents a kilo.

At this time of year, we're completely empty, and it's not enough. I need to borrow a few thousand acres from another co-op to satisfy my customers. Every day there are several large trucks in and out pull vegetables, every day at least 70 tons of processing, sold to Beijing, Guangzhou, Chongqing, Shaanxi, Shanxi, Shandong and other places.

Now there are only three customers, mostly local wholesalers in Jingmen. Many places can not get out, said a car stuck in the mouth of the village, or in the road block up more than one meter high Earth Dam do not let go.

Ten days ago, a wholesaler in Wuhan asked me for a batch of Chinese cabbage. He got a big truck from another place to pull 18 tons of Chinese cabbage. He refused to let me pass on the way back. Finally, he had no way to make a detour and ran an extra eighty kilometers.

Cars from other provinces couldn't get in. I called the wholesalers that Guangzhou and Chongqing often work with. They said Hubei was a disaster area, so they couldn't get food from Hubei, and they couldn't.

Watching the food go bad day by day makes me sad. More than 100 Mu of Artemisia Sphaerocephala are now Rotary Tiller spin off. The last time I turned the lettuce in the shed, my wife was standing there crying and not saying anything. The vegetables, which were planted last August, employ thirty workers a day and cost more than 2,000 yuan per mu of land.

Hubei is a big vegetable province, too many people grow vegetables, the price of vegetables also can not go up, I have lost for 3 years in a row.

These two days, we are going to use the land we used to grow Artemisia to grow Chili peppers, so we moved to live near the vegetable fields. Worry Ah, a day 3 packs of cigarettes can not stop, night smoking more, can not sleep has been watching TV, open TV are talking about the epidemic. I woke up at 4:00 in the morning, got up, held a flashlight and went to the vegetable plot to see how bad the food was. It was dark outside, and there were only a few birdcalls now and then, and I was walking alone in the vegetable patch.

Spring ploughing is coming. There is not much money to be put into it now. When the time comes, we will borrow some more from our relatives and friends. We have lent some money in the past. We are all too embarrassed to ask. Let us consider these matters after a period of time. For the time being, we will free up more than 1,000 mu of land.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After the outbreak was closed to management, village committees or communities in a position to do so helped farmers find ways to sell their vegetables. Screenshot of the cover news video

"150 catties of Seaweed Moss donated to the city. "

Chung cheung-choi, Lee do-chui, 48

On the morning of the first day of the New Year, more than 10:00 am, the village suddenly stopped a silver-gray car, the loudspeaker announced that the village closed, I just know the city that pneumonia serious.

At lunch time, his wife sighed and said, "If we keep closing the village, how can we get our food out? " At that time, there were nearly 3 mu of garlic plants in our field that had not yet grown up and were not even tied up to 1 kg. Our family a total of 6 mu 8 field, other cabbage, radish scattered scattered planted a mu or two mu, usually after the sale of vegetables. I think the food is almost done, and the village is unsealed.

Turns out, I didn't think it would be this bad.

The garlic in the field adds up to nearly 6000 Jin, began to grow moss slowly, my wife and I are anxious, every day to remove grass, pull moss. Garlic is very tired, from the beginning of the lunar calendar in July sowing, after several times weeding, to now pull moss, we have to bend one by one, one day down backache, small business, reluctant to find workers help, when the time is not easy to calculate.

Our entire village of Liangqiao village 12 groups of more than 60 households, young people have gone outside, the remaining old people mainly to plant garlic seedlings, together there are nearly 100 mu garlic seedlings, this loss is very big.

As usual, after Chinese New Year, the two of US tied up all the garlic seedlings in the field. My wife would drive a tricycle to pull 200-300 Jin, walk more than 20 minutes to the city and set up a stall. During Chinese New Year, the price in the city could rise to 1 yuan per Jin, almost every day can be sold out, months to time all the garlic can be emptied.

We have no channel to sell vegetables, I heard that these days outside of the food sold very expensive. We don't know the greengrocers, we know the big platforms, but they don't know us. Usually pull themselves to the city to sell scattered, sometimes met the boss, as long as take more, lower prices, we also sell, can not let the vegetables bad in the field. In this way, the garlic shoots can be sold for more than 10,000 yuan a year. Years ago also think, this year to sell the garlic seedlings, to buy some goods, usually want to eat expensive things, only in the new year to buy.

My wife and I grow vegetables for a year's income. My son runs a small restaurant in the city that specializes in crispy-skin chicken and roast rice. He takes take-out food. He sleeps at 3 a.m. and gets up at 8 a.m. or 9 a.m. every day. His daughter-in-law works all night as a waitress at a KTV, they earn enough to feed themselves, and they work hard. Black eye is very heavy, but also to pay the mortgage, usually no time to come back, sometimes we will carry vegetables to the city to see them, also do not dare to disturb.

This year they came back to the original plan to leave the third day, but closed the village did not go. Actually, I'm very happy, as a family. I told my son how much I cherish these days.

A few days ago, the son posted a post on the Internet, the photo of our garlic plant uploaded, the next day there are many people to call us, said to want garlic plant. I am very glad, take advantage of the garlic sprout does not have full length moss, still can handle out. But then I couldn't even negotiate the price, so I couldn't. The main thing is, they can't get their cars in, we can't get them out, and we still haven't sold them for a dime.

For us, such retail investors, there is not too much impact, but the next year the quality of life is a little worse than we lost many people.

On the 15th day of the first lunar month, the village committee launched a donation meeting. We donated 100 yuan by mobile phone, and then pulled 150 catties of Seaweed Moss to the brigade. They then pulled out to donate to the community in the city.

If the vegetable really sell out, we also accept, the son often said, as long as we are saved, the vegetable does not sell out does not matter.

I think so, but still want to unseal, this garlic can sell the best, how low price is OK.
